==French==
===Pronunciation===
* IPA: /ɡlu.tɔ̃/
* SAMPA: /glu.to~/
* X-SAMPA: /glu."tO~/
*{{audio|Fr-glouton-fr-FR-Paris.ogg|Audio (Parisian)}}

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[gluto]]'' or ''[[glutto]]'' of the same meaning, from ''[[glutus]]'' or ''[[gluttus]]'' meaning "throat" and "absorption"

===Adjective===
'''glouton''' {{m}}, '''[[gloutonne]]''' {{f}} (''plural:'' '''[[gloutons]]''' {{m}}, '''[[gloutonnes]]''' {{f}})

# (''of a man or animal'') [[gluttonous|Gluttonous]]; devouring or engulfing one's food greedily.
#:* Cet enfant a toujours été '''glouton'''.
#:*:''This child has always been gluttonous.''
#:* Le loup est un animal '''glouton'''.
#:*:''The wolf is a gluttonous animal.
# (''figuratively'') [[gluttonous|Gluttonous]]; having a great greed toward something.
#:* Avec de prodigieuse vitesse de réaction, certaines enzymes sont '''gloutonnes''' en substrat.
#:*:''With an extaordianry reaction rate, certain enzymes are gluttonous of their substrate.''

====Synonyms====
*(''devouring or englufing food''): [[goinfre]], [[goulu]], [[vorace]]
*(''having great greed''): [[avide]]

====Derived terms====
* [[gloutonnerie]]
* [[gloutonnement]]

===Noun===
'''glouton''' {{m}}, '''[[gloutonne]]''' {{f}}, (''plural:'' '''[[gloutons]]''' {{m}}, '''[[gloutonnes]]''' {{f}})

# [[glutton|Glutton]]; a person or animal who eats his food greedily.
#:* Ce '''glouton''' se jette sur son assiette.
#:*:''This glutton throws himself onto his plate.''

===Etymology===
Substantive of the adjective, in relation to the behavior and voracity of the animal

===Noun===
[[Image:Wolverine.jpg|thumb|A glutton ('''glouton''').]]
'''glouton''' (''plural:'' '''[[gloutons]]''')

# (''Zoology'') [[glutton|Glutton]], a mammalian carnivore of the Arctic regions resembling a small bear with a hairy tail.
#:* Le '''glouton''' est un animal solitaire.
#:*:''The glutton is a solitary animal.''

====Synonyms====
* (''glutton''): [[carcajou]]

